	<div class="content">
        <h3>The Centre</h3>
		<p>The Centre is a multifunctional community space managed by Grace Mission International that facilitates many groups and local service providers in the area. The Centre is ideal for up to 70 guests for conferences, workshops, classes and parties. The Centre facilities comprise of one main hall, a kitchen and toilets. The Centre is available to rent and to make a book enquiry please <a href="#contact-foot">contact us</a>.<p>
		<p>We have hosted: Barnet Refugee Service, Resources for Autism, Grace Mission International, Colindale Foodbank &amp; Christian Against Poverty (CAP).
</p>
 
		<h3>CAP (Christians Against Poverty)</h3>
		<p>Our CAP debt centre provides vital support to those struggling with debt large or small. The CAP team know and understand the stress of life when you are stuck in debt and they are available to provide the vital support and help you need to get your life back on track.</p>
        <p>To book an appointment please contact us on 0800 328 0006.</p>
		
		<p><strong>See how our CAP debt centre helped Aaron:</strong></p>
		
		<div class="videoWrapper">
			<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/245362685" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>

 
		<h3>Foodbank (Trussell Trust):</h3>
		<p>Thirteen million people live below the poverty line in the UK, with individuals going hungry every day for a range of reasons, from benefit delays to receiving an unexpected bill on a low income. The Trussell Trust’s 400-strong network of foodbanks provides a minimum of three days’ emergency food and support to people experiencing crisis in the UK. In 2015/16, we gave 1,109,309 three day emergency food supplies to people in crisis.</p>
        <p>The <a href="http://colindale.foodbank.org.uk" target="_blank">Foodbank</a> is open between 12-2:30pm every Tuesday and Thursday at The Centre.</p>
		
